- AngularJS is the Client Side JavaScript Framework.

- AngularJS Follows the MVC Design Pattern.

    M - Model    (JavaScript Variables)
                 Ex.
                        var i = 100;

    V - View     (HTML / HTML5)

    C - Controllers (JavaScript Functions)
                    Ex.
                        function ctrl(){
                            //Business Logic
                         }

- Angular Framework have a so many predefined Modules,As a Angular Developer we
  can use the Predefined Modules.


  1. ngAnimate
        used to develop the Animations in angular applications

  2. ngStorage
        used to work with the browser storages.
        browser have two types of storages.
            1.localStorage
            2.sessionStorage

  3.ngMessage
       used to handle the client side form validations

  4.ngRoute
        used to implement the Routing in Single Page Application.

        now a days no body using ngRoute Module because of it's limitations.


  5.ui.router
        used to implement the Routing in Single Page Applications.

        now a days all most all the projects they are using ui.router module,
        because of it's advantages.


 Ex. Develop the Angular Application with the Following Features

        1. Animations Support

        2. Validations Support

        3. Storages Support

        4. SPA (ui.router)


index.html
-
<!DOCTYPE html>
 <html ng-app="app">

    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/angularjs/1.6.4/angular.min.js"></script>
    <script>
       var obj =
                angular.module("app",["ui.router",
                                       "ngAnimate",
                                       "ngMessages",
                                       "ngStorage]);
    </script>
 </html>




















